Sprint Goal 

The goal of this 2-week sprint is to deliver a functional Minimum Viable Product (MVP) by implementing core system features, including user authentication, appointment scheduling, appointment approval workflows, and attendance recording.

This sprint focuses on enabling basic interaction between students and lecturers, ensuring the system provides immediate value and validates usability.

 Selected User Stories (Sprint 1)

The following high-priority (Must-have) user stories are selected for this sprint:

US-001: Login
US-002: Book Appointment
US-003: Approve Appointment
US-004: Record Attendance

These stories were selected because they represent the core functionality required for the system to operate.

