 Sprint Burndown Concept
A Sprint Burndown Chart will be used to track progress throughout the sprint.

The total estimated work (in hours) is tracked daily.
Remaining work is updated as tasks are completed.
The chart visually shows whether the team is on track or falling behind schedule.

 This helps:

Identify delays early
Improve team productivity
Ensure sprint goals are achieved within the time frame

Sprint Contribution to MVP
This sprint contributes directly to the development of a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) by implementing the system’s most essential features.

At the end of the sprint, the system will allow:

Students to log in and book appointments
Lecturers to approve or reject appointment requests
Lecturers to record student attendance

These functionalities represent the core value of the system, enabling real interaction between users and validating that the system meets its primary objectives.

Delivering these features early ensures:

Quick validation of system usability
Early feedback for improvement
A strong foundation for future enhancements![alt text](image-1.png)